Thank you for considering Lost Key Golf Club and Grille 625 as the venue for your special event. Our dedicated team is passionate about ensuring that your celebration is both joyful and unforgettable. Book today to begin planning your perfect occasion!
Our goal is to ensure that every detail is meticulously addressed. We take pride not only in the quality of our amenities but also in the personalized service, professionalism, and attention to detail demonstrated by our club staff. We are confident that when you choose Lost Key Golf Club and Grille 625 as your event venue, you will create lasting memories to cherish for years to come
For more information on hosting your outing or event at Lost Key Golf Club, please call (850) 549-2160
or email
mnelson@lostkeygolf.com

**Member cart fee is $24.00 plus tax for 18 holes, $12.00 for 9 holes. Walking is permitted at discretion of manager before 1:00 p.m. Private cart fee is $125.00 monthly. Bag storage and locker fees are $120.00 each per year. Billing occurs on the first of the month for prior months dues and charges. There is a quarterly F&B minimum of $150.00 for regular members, $75.00 for Transfer members. Members are required to sign for charges to their account and must have a credit card on file whether they pay by credit card or not. Monthly charges paid by credit/debit card are subject to a $10 monthly charge. All payments are subject to Florida sales tax of 7.5%.
Transferable memberships have the same Initiation Fees as the Single and Family.
Contact:
Ricky White
Membership Director
Rwhite
@lostkeygolf.com
Office 850.549.2165
GHIN Service
Our Premier membership opportunities are for seasoned players or those just starting out. We have Single, Family or Transferable memberships for individuals who have a vacation home and choose to rent their home when not in town. Additionally, we have Corporate Memberships for local businesses looking to expand their network with like-minded professionals who share a passion for the game of Golf and all of the benefits of being a Member. All of the current Memberships are available to non-residents of Lost Key and the general public.
Members enjoy the following privileges:
Advanced fourteen-day preferred tee times
Use of locker rooms with showers/bathrooms with television and game table
Complimentary handicapping system
Complimentary charging privileges
Complimentary greens fees
Preferred pricing on golf shop merchandise,  15% off Apparel, Head-wear and Footwear
Preferred rate for member accompanied guests
Unlimited use of members-only practice range facility with unlimited range balls
Ability to utilize facility for corporate meetings and events
Access to member/guest and member club events

For those who live for the experience and have a passion for the game there is no equal to Lost Key Golf Club.
/wp:heading
wp:paragraph
Framed by the natural beauty of Perdido Key, Lost Key is ideally located between historic downtown Pensacola and the pristine sugar sand beaches of Orange Beach and Gulf Shores.
/wp:paragraph
wp:paragraph
Redesigned by the Arnold Palmer Design Group in 2006, the par 71 signature designed championship course features  Sea Dwarf Paspalum grass from the tee through the green for the optimum in quality playing surfaces and green speeds. Each golf hole includes five sets of tees, and offers players of all skill levels a unique visual and strategic playing experience.
/wp:paragraph
wp:paragraph
Lost Key was the first golf course in the State of Florida to be certified as an Audubon International Silver Signature Sanctuary. The project continues to protect the natural resources of the area while providing an outstanding golf experience.
/wp:paragraph
wp:paragraph
Our new state-of-the-art golf clubhouse features a full-service golf shop, men’s and ladies locker room facilities with lounge areas, and Grille 625,  a restaurant and bar with indoor and outdoor seating and panoramic views of the golf course. Lost Key Golf Club provides all the amenities and quality service of the finest private clubs, yet is open to non-Members and resort guests. Lost Key welcomes golf outings of all sizes and our clubhouse is available for private social events.
ATM in Lobby (Hours 7am – 6pm)
